# Deployment Workflow Rules

## Git Workflow

### Branch Strategy
```bash
# 1. Create feature branch from main
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b feature/descriptive-name

# 2. Make changes and test locally
npm run dev
npm run lint
npm run build

# 3. Commit with descriptive message
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add user authentication flow

- Add JWT token generation
- Implement login/logout routes
- Add user session management
- Fix #123"

# 4. Push to remote
git push origin feature/descriptive-name

# 5. Create Pull Request on GitHub
```

### Branch Naming Conventions
```bash
feature/user-authentication    # New features
fix/console-log-removal        # Bug fixes
refactor/database-queries      # Code refactoring
docs/update-readme            # Documentation
chore/update-dependencies     # Maintenance
```

### Commit Message Format
Follow conventional commits:
```bash
# Format: <type>: <description>
#
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer]

# Types:
feat:     # New feature
fix:      # Bug fix
refactor: # Code refactoring
docs:     # Documentation
style:    # Formatting, missing semicolons, etc.
test:     # Adding tests
chore:    # Maintenance

# Examples:
feat: add product listing page
fix: resolve console.log statements in auth
refactor: use TABLE_NAMES constants in queries
docs: update API documentation
```

## Protected Files

### Never Commit These
```bash
# ❌ Never commit:
.env
.env.local
.env.production
*.log
*.pid
node_modules/
.DS_Store
.vscode/settings.json (if contains personal config)
```

### Protected Branches
- **main** - Production branch (protected)
- **develop** - Development branch (optional)

**Rules:**
- No direct commits to `main`
- All changes via Pull Requests
- Require at least 1 approval (for teams)
- CI/CD must pass

## Pre-Commit Checklist

### Before Every Commit
```bash
# 1. Verify no console.log statements
grep -r "console\." src/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"

# 2. Check linting
npm run lint

# 3. Verify TypeScript compilation
npm run build

# 4. Run tests (if applicable)
npm run test

# 5. Check git status
git status

# 6. Review changes
git diff
```

### File-Specific Checks
- **Migration files**: Never delete or modify existing ones
- **Config files**: Verify no hardcoded credentials
- **Components**: Check for proper error handling
- **API routes**: Ensure logger is used (not console.log)

## Deployment Process

### Local to Vercel (Production)

#### 1. Prepare for Deployment
```bash
# Clean build
rm -rf .next
npm run build

# Verify environment variables
cat .env.production.local  # Do NOT commit this file

# Test production build locally
npm run start
```

#### 2. Merge to Main
```bash
# Ensure feature branch is up-to-date
git checkout feature/your-feature
git pull origin main
git rebase main  # Resolve any conflicts

# Merge via Pull Request on GitHub
# - Add clear PR description
# - Link related issues
# - Request review
```

#### 3. Automatic Deployment
Vercel automatically deploys from `main` branch:
- Commit to `main` → Automatic deployment
- Preview deployments for PRs
- Check deployment status on Vercel dashboard

#### 4. Post-Deployment Verification
```bash
# Visit production site
# Check these pages:
https://revamp-it.ch
https://revamp-it.ch/admin
https://revamp-it.ch/shop/medusa

# Verify:
- [ ] Site loads correctly
- [ ] No console errors in browser
- [ ] Database connections work
- [ ] Authentication works
- [ ] API routes respond
```

### Database Migrations

#### Before Deploying Database Changes
```bash
# 1. Test migration locally
PGPASSWORD=$POSTGRES_PASSWORD psql -h localhost -p 5433 -U postgres -d revampit_cms < cms-api/src/migrations/XXX_migration.sql

# 2. Verify schema changes
\d table_name

# 3. Test application with new schema
npm run dev

# 4. Create backup (production)
# Backup database before running migrations in production
```

#### Migration Deployment
```bash
# Production migration (careful!)
# 1. Create database backup first
# 2. Run migration script
# 3. Verify application works
# 4. Monitor for errors
```

## Environment Variables

### Required Variables
```bash
# Database
DATABASE_URL=
POSTGRES_HOST=
POSTGRES_PORT=5433
POSTGRES_DB=revampit_cms
POSTGRES_USER=postgres
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=

# Medusa
MEDUSA_DATABASE_URL=
MEDUSA_PASSWORD=

# Authentication
JWT_SECRET=
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=
NEXTAUTH_URL=

# Email (optional)
SMTP_HOST=
SMTP_PORT=
SMTP_USER=
SMTP_PASSWORD=
```

### Environment Management
- **Local**: `.env.local` (gitignored)
- **Production**: Vercel dashboard → Environment Variables
- **Never commit**: Any file with credentials

## Rollback Procedure

### If Deployment Fails
```bash
# 1. Revert commit on main
git revert HEAD
git push origin main

# 2. Or force push previous working commit
git reset --hard <previous-commit-hash>
git push origin main --force  # Use with caution!

# 3. Vercel will automatically redeploy
```

### Database Rollback
```bash
# If migration fails:
# 1. Restore from backup
# 2. Verify application works
# 3. Fix migration script
# 4. Test again locally
```

## CI/CD Checks

### Automated Checks (GitHub Actions)
```yaml
# Runs on every PR and push to main:
- Lint check (npm run lint)
- Type check (npm run build)
- Tests (npm run test)
- Build verification

# Only deploy if all checks pass
```

## Emergency Procedures

### If Production is Down
1. Check Vercel deployment logs
2. Check database connectivity
3. Verify environment variables
4. Check for runtime errors
5. Rollback if necessary

### Quick Fixes
```bash
# Hot fix process:
git checkout -b hotfix/critical-bug
# Fix the issue
git commit -m "hotfix: resolve critical production bug"
git push origin hotfix/critical-bug
# Create PR, get quick review, merge to main
```

## Important Reminders

### Never
- ❌ Commit directly to `main`
- ❌ Force push to `main` (unless emergency rollback)
- ❌ Delete migration files
- ❌ Commit `.env` files
- ❌ Deploy without testing locally
- ❌ Deploy without running linter
- ❌ Skip CI/CD checks

### Always
- ✅ Create feature branches
- ✅ Write descriptive commit messages
- ✅ Test locally before pushing
- ✅ Run linter before committing
- ✅ Create Pull Requests
- ✅ Wait for CI/CD checks to pass
- ✅ Backup database before migrations
- ✅ Verify production after deployment
